{"title":"Salsaâ€™s 2021 Warbird and Stormchaser Have New Colors and Build Specs","link":"https://theradavist.com/2021/03/salsas-2021-warbird-and-stormchaser-have-new-colors-and-build-specs/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=salsas-2021-warbird-and-stormchaser-have-new-colors-and-build-specs","date":1615476664000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210126_SAL_Warbird_Studio_707647_003_cc.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206900\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210126_SAL_Warbird_Studio_707647_003_cc.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210126_SAL_Warbird_Studio_707647_003_cc.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210126_SAL_Warbird_Studio_707647_003_cc.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210126_SAL_Warbird_Studio_707647_003_cc.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210126_SAL_Warbird_Studio_707647_003_cc.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210126_SAL_Warbird_Studio_707647_003_cc.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210126_SAL_Warbird_Studio_707647_003_cc.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /></p>\n<p>Salsa&#8217;s flagship gravel bikes are back this year with new paint and new specs. The all-carbon Warbird still fits a 700c x 45 mm or 650b x 2.0&#8243; with a racey geometry. New for 2021, the Warbird comes laced with AXS wide ($6,999) at the top end or Apex 1 ($2,799).</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210127_SAL_Stormchaser_Studio_707647_001_cc.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-206902\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210127_SAL_Stormchaser_Studio_707647_001_cc.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210127_SAL_Stormchaser_Studio_707647_001_cc.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210127_SAL_Stormchaser_Studio_707647_001_cc.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210127_SAL_Stormchaser_Studio_707647_001_cc.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210127_SAL_Stormchaser_Studio_707647_001_cc.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210127_SAL_Stormchaser_Studio_707647_001_cc.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/03/20210127_SAL_Stormchaser_Studio_707647_001_cc.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" /></p>\n<p>The aluminum Stormchaser can cram a little bigger tires at 700c x 50 mm or 650b x 50 mm, yet is designed to be raced in muddy conditions with a 42mm tire for ample mud clearance. The Stormchaser also has a slacker head angle to battle the muck. The Stormchaser comes built as shown as a singlespeed ($1599) or as a frameset with a geared or singlespeed option ($1199).</p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://salsacycles.com/culture/fresh_gravel_new_warbird_stormchaser\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Salsa</a>.</p>","author":"prolly","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"2dbeac19e823a66e1e5e0ea25b7f1096ada83b7273f59fd8443355c881f5f3e5","category":"Cycling"}